This will be a binary mock-up file for which driver should be responsible for each files runtime.
This will involve a wine-like system,
But instead it's entirely kernel-sided.

Will this break many, many windows apps that expect specific Windows-related quirks?
Yes ABSOLUTELY.

Is it a more modern approach?
Probably?

This hasn't even begun yet.

This will also allow you to run MacOS & GNU-style apps in the future via sandboxxing.
The driver for GNU will just be a namespace.

Of course, this, you can't interact with.

Check out /ZubiOS/Bin/CL!
